						Focused Investors LLC Sells 105,600 Shares of Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) (NYSE:GS)					

						 July 28th, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Stacy Sanders 


							Filed Under: Finance - SEC Filing Articles 







Tweet










Focused Investors LLC cut its position in  Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) (NYSE:GS) by 19.6% during the second quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 432,600 shares of the investment management company’s stock after selling 105,600 shares during the period. Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) comprises approximately  4.1% of Focused Investors LLC’s holdings, making the stock its 15th largest position. Focused Investors LLC owned 0.11% of Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) worth $95,994,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Other institutional investors have also recently made changes to their positions in the company. Parallel Advisors LLC increased its position in shares of  Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) by 10.7% in the first quarter. Parallel Advisors LLC now owns 558 shares of the investment management company’s stock worth $126,000 after buying an additional 54 shares in the last quarter.  YorkBridge Wealth Partners LLC increased its position in shares of  Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) by 0.3% in the first quarter. YorkBridge Wealth Partners LLC now owns 640 shares of the investment management company’s stock worth $144,000 after buying an additional 2 shares in the last quarter.  Franklin Parlapiano Turner & Welch LLC purchased a new position in shares of  Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) during the first quarter worth approximately $161,000.  Quadrant Capital Group LLC increased its position in shares of  Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) by 11.5% in the first quarter. Quadrant Capital Group LLC now owns 875 shares of the investment management company’s stock worth $192,000 after buying an additional 90 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Cheviot Value Management LLC purchased a new position in shares of  Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) during the first quarter worth approximately $203,000. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  74.20% of the company’s stock. 
Shares of Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (GS) opened at 221.48 on Friday. The firm has a 50-day moving average price of $223.65 and a 200 day moving average price of $230.54. The stock has a market cap of $89.23 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 11.61 and a beta of 1.42. Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. has a 52-week low of $155.37 and a 52-week high of $255.15. 




Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) (NYSE:GS) last released its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, July 18th. The investment management company reported $3.95 EPS for the quarter, topping the consensus estimate of $3.39 by $0.56. The company had revenue of $7.89 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $7.47 billion. Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) had a return on equity of 11.25% and a net margin of 26.44%. The firm’s revenue was down .6% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter in the previous year, the company posted $3.72 earnings per share.  Analysts expect that  Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. will post $18.28 earnings per share for the current year. 
Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) declared that its Board of Directors has authorized a stock repurchase plan on Tuesday, April 18th that authorizes the company to repurchase 50,000,000 outstanding  shares. This repurchase authorization authorizes the investment management company to purchase shares of its stock through open market purchases. Stock  repurchase plans are often a sign that the company’s management believes its stock is undervalued. 
The business also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Thursday, September 28th. Shareholders of record on Thursday, August 31st will be paid a $0.75 dividend. This represents a $3.00 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 1.35%. Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The)’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is currently 15.74%. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: “Focused Investors LLC Sells 105,600 Shares of Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) (NYSE:GS)” was  published by Daily Political and is the sole property of of Daily Political. If you are viewing this article on another website, it was stolen and republished in violation of U.S. & international copyright and trademark legislation. The legal version of this article can be accessed at https://www.dailypolitical.com/2017/07/28/focused-investors-llc-sells-105600-shares-of-goldman-sachs-group-inc-the-nysegs.html. 
GS has been the subject of a number of recent research reports. UBS AG  reiterated a “buy” rating and issued a $285.00 target price on shares of Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) in a report on Wednesday, April 19th. Bank of America Corporation reduced their target price on shares of Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) from $275.00 to $265.00 and set a “buy” rating for the company in a report on Wednesday, April 19th. Credit Suisse Group  reiterated a “buy” rating on shares of Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) in a report on Wednesday, April 19th. HSBC Holdings plc  reiterated a “buy” rating and issued a $275.00 target price on shares of Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) in a report on Tuesday, April 25th. Finally, Keefe, Bruyette & Woods  set a $260.00 target price on shares of Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) and gave the stock a “buy” rating in a report on Saturday, May 6th. Three investment analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, fifteen have issued  a hold rating, twelve have issued  a buy rating and one  has given a strong buy rating to the stock. The company  has an average rating of “Hold” and an average target price of $235.25.
About Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The)
The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc is an investment banking, securities and investment management company that provides a range of financial services to corporations, financial institutions, governments and individuals. The Company operates in four business segments: Investment Banking, Institutional Client Services, Investing & Lending, and Investment Management.
